                                     "date":  "2026-05-30T11:26:00Z"
                                 },
                   "message":  "GENERIC-LATEST-HANDOFF: unify the three latest-only handoffs into Handoff\u003cT\u003e\n\nRenderHandoff, InspectorHandoff, and SaveStatusHandoff were three\nbyte-identical hand-written copies of a Mutex\u003cOption\u003cArc\u003cT\u003e\u003e\u003e + AtomicU64\nlatest-only slot (Rule of Three). This collapses the mechanism into one\ngeneric Handoff\u003cT\u003e in rge-editor-state — the only crate both editor-shell and\neditor-egui-host depend on — and keeps the three names as type aliases at\ntheir sites, so every call site is unchanged.\n\n- editor-state: new handoff.rs (generic Handoff\u003cT\u003e + 9-test mechanism suite);\n  lib.rs registers + re-exports it, with a doc note that it is dep-neutral\n  shared infrastructure, not a 6th coordination category.\n- editor-shell/render_input.rs: RenderHandoff is now\n  `type RenderHandoff = Handoff\u003cRenderInputOwned\u003e`; the (ecs_tick,\n  checkpoint_id) anchor stays a RenderInputOwned payload field.\n- editor-egui-host/handoff.rs: InspectorHandoff / SaveStatusHandoff become\n  aliases; the redundant in-file mechanism tests are removed (covered once by\n  the generic suite); the verbatim-copy doctrine prose is retired.\n- editor-egui-host/lib.rs: doc prose refreshed (no more \"mirrors RenderHandoff\n  shape\" / \"verbatim sibling\").\n\nConsistent with ADR-117: semantics preserved; sub-decision 5 / non-decision 6\nexplicitly defer the crate/primitive choice, so no ADR edit. No Cargo.toml\nchange, no new dependency, no unsafe. Behavior delta: Debug/panic strings are\nnow generic \"Handoff\" (no test asserts the type-name string). All existing\nADR-117 boundary + host/tab integration tests pass unchanged via the aliases.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
